{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"YEOFR"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"QuickStart"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Recognise the enrolled user and reject everyone else, in a few lines.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"1. Add the SDK","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"1-Add-the-SDK"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"YEOFR"}]},{"text":" Swift package","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"https:\/\/github.com\/YEOMessaging\/YEOFR-SPM","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") to your project, pinned to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"exact version ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.5.8"}]},{"text":", then ","type":"text"},{"code":"import YEOFR","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The binary is ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"arm64"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device-only"}]},{"text":" — it does not run on the simulator.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"2. Pilot unlock for non-YEO bundle IDs","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"2-Pilot-unlock-for-non-YEO-bundle-IDs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"YEOFR is gated to YEO-owned apps by default; a non-YEO bundle id aborts on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"construction. Evaluation customers get a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"temporary unlock code"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bypasses the gate during a fixed pilot window — email","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"christo@yeomessaging.com"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" to request one. Pass it to the initializer","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(step 3). YEO-owned apps pass the gate natively and do not need a code.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"3-Drive-everything-with-FaceTrustService","text":"3. Drive everything with `FaceTrustService`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is the turnkey entry point. It owns the engine, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"camera, the fused-trust pipeline (face recognition + liveness CNN +"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TrueDepth), the identity gate, and tracker persistence, and exposes two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"streams: one for live trust verdicts and one for guided enrolment."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import YEOFR","","let service = FaceTrustService(pilotUnlockCode: \"YOUR-PILOT-CODE\")","","\/\/ Attach the preview to an AVCaptureVideoPreviewLayer:","\/\/   previewLayer.session = service.previewSession","","try await service.start()    \/\/ warm-up, restore enrolment, arm gate, start camera"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"4-Enrol-a-face","text":"4. Enrol a face"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"enroll(name:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs a short guided capture, persists the gallery, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"re-arms the identity gate. Iterate the returned stream to coach the user:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["for await step in service.enroll(name: \"Alice\") {","    switch step.phase {","    case .capturing: show(step.prompt, progress: step.poseProgress)","    case .completed: dismiss()","    case .failed:    show(step.prompt)","    @unknown default: break","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A single front pose is enough to separate the enrolled user from other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"people. Pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"poses: PoseTarget.lightingAwareGallerySequence","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to also","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capture off-axis poses + a lighting pass, which improves recall as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user turns their head."}]},{"level":2,"text":"5. Run live recognition","anchor":"5-Run-live-recognition","type":"heading"},{"code":["for await update in service.updates() {","    switch update.status {","    case .trusted:    badge(\"TRUSTED — \\(update.matchedName ?? \"\")\", .green)","    case .notTrusted: badge(\"NOT TRUSTED\", .red)","    case .badFraming: badge(\"ADJUST FRAMING\", .orange)","    case .noFace:     badge(\"NO FACE\", .gray)","    @unknown default: break","    }","    \/\/ update.livenessGenuine \/ update.depthIsThreeD are the contributing signals.","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update.status == .trusted"},{"type":"text","text":" already fuses face recognition, liveness, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TrueDepth, with framing applied — you never pick a similarity threshold,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and you never touch the identity gate (forgetting it would collapse trust"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to liveness + depth, so any live face would pass). The enrolled gallery is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"saved across launches automatically; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"service.enrolledName"},{"type":"text","text":" reflects who is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"enrolled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"See also","anchor":"See-also","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A complete, runnable SwiftUI app lives in the package’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/FRPilot"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService","isActive":true},{"text":" — full API.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustUpdate","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/EnrollmentProgress"},{"text":" — the stream payloads.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/QuickStart","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/quickstart"]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/quickstart"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService"],"title":"Getting started","anchor":"Getting-started","generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://com.yeomessaging.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"On-device face recognition with fused liveness and TrueDepth anti-spoofing."}],"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR","title":"YEOFR","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr","kind":"symbol"},"doc://com.yeomessaging.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustUpdate":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FaceTrustUpdate","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FaceTrustUpdate","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustUpdate","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustupdate","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"One per-frame trust readout, with the framing gate already applied — so the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consumer renders a state, not a fusion of raw signals. Yielded by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/updates()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"title":"FaceTrustUpdate","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://com.yeomessaging.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustService/enroll(name:poses:)":{"title":"enroll(name:poses:)","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/enroll(name:poses:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enroll"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"name"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"poses"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:5YEOFR10PoseTargetO","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PoseTarget"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"AsyncStream"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:5YEOFR18EnrollmentProgressV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnrollmentProgress"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Enrol ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"type":"text","text":" from the live camera and return a stream of capture"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. The existing frame loop drives the gallery walk; on completion"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the service persists the gallery, refreshes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enrolledName"},{"type":"text","text":", resets the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trust pipeline against the fresh gallery, and re-arms the identity gate —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the consumer does none of that."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustservice\/enroll(name:poses:)"},"doc://com.yeomessaging.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/EnrollmentProgress":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/enrollmentprogress","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/EnrollmentProgress","title":"EnrollmentProgress","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EnrollmentProgress","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EnrollmentProgress","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Progress for an in-flight enrolment capture. Yielded by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/enroll(name:poses:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" and the stream finishes once the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"gallery is banked (or the capture can’t start).","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.yeomessaging.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustService":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustservice","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FaceTrustService","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Turnkey entry point for on-device face recognition with fused liveness","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and TrueDepth anti-spoofing.","type":"text"}],"title":"FaceTrustService","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FaceTrustService","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://com.yeomessaging.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustService/updates()":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"updates"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"AsyncStream","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"FaceTrustUpdate","preciseIdentifier":"s:5YEOFR15FaceTrustUpdateV"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Per-frame trust verdicts for the recognition UI. Call once and iterate;","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the stream finishes on ","type":"text"},{"code":"stop()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Newest-wins (the underlying camera","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stream drops stale frames), so a slow consumer can’t back up memory.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.yeomessaging.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/updates()","title":"updates()","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustservice\/updates()","kind":"symbol"}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"value":"occ","op":"replace","path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage"},{"value":null,"op":"add","path":"\/topicSections"},{"value":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":[],"title":"Getting started","anchor":"Getting-started"}],"op":"replace","path":"\/seeAlsoSections"}]}]}